
.TH WATCHGUARD 8 "2026-07-03" "watchguard 1.0.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
watchguard \- plugin-based host health monitor for systemd Linux servers

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B watchguard
.I COMMAND
.RI [ OPTIONS ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B watchguard
is a lightweight Rust-based host health monitor for systemd Linux servers.

It can monitor SSH service health, SSH TCP reachability, outbound network reachability, DNS resolution, and OOM events observed through journald.

Watchguard can restart SSH or reboot the host depending on configuration. Reboot actions are protected by boot grace and reboot cooldown settings.

By default, all plugin sections are present in the configuration but disabled. This makes a fresh install safe until the administrator explicitly enables checks.

.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B watchguard daemon [--config PATH]
Run Watchguard as a foreground daemon. This is normally started by systemd.

.TP
.B watchguard status [--config PATH]
Show enabled plugins and current probe status.

.TP
.B watchguard doctor [--config PATH]
Run diagnostic checks for config syntax, required commands, systemd, journald, and enabled plugin prerequisites.

.TP
.B watchguard test [--config PATH] [--all]
Run plugin probes once and exit. By default, only enabled plugins are tested. With
.BR --all ,
all configured plugins are tested even if they are disabled.

.TP
.B watchguard logs [--unit UNIT] [--since TIME] [-n LINES] [-b|--boot] [--no-follow]
Show Watchguard logs through journalctl. By default this follows
.BR watchguard.service .

.TP
.B watchguard version
Print Watchguard version and build metadata.

.TP
.B watchguard enable PLUGIN [--config PATH]
Enable a plugin or sub-check.

.TP
.B watchguard disable PLUGIN [--remove] [--config PATH]
Disable a plugin or sub-check. With
.BR --remove ,
remove the plugin configuration table.

.TP
.B watchguard config init [--force] [--config PATH]
Create a default configuration file.

.TP
.B watchguard config show [--config PATH]
Print the active configuration.

.TP
.B watchguard config validate [--config PATH]
Validate the configuration file.

.TP
.B watchguard config edit [--config PATH]
Open the configuration in
.BR $EDITOR ,
or
.B vi
if EDITOR is unset.

.SH PLUGINS
.TP
.B ssh
Enables both SSH service and SSH target checks.

.TP
.B ssh-service
Enables or disables only the systemd SSH service-state check.

.TP
.B ssh-targets
Enables or disables only SSH TCP target reachability checks.

.TP
.B network
Checks outbound TCP reachability to configured targets.

.TP
.B dns
Checks DNS resolution through a configured DNS server.

.TP
.B oom
Watches journald for OOM messages.

.SH CONFIGURATION
The default configuration file is:

.EX
/etc/watchguard/config.toml
.EE

Durations use human-readable strings:

.EX
500ms
2s
30s
1m
5m
30m
1h
.EE

.SH GLOBAL CONFIGURATION
Example:

.EX
[global]
log_level = "info"
boot_grace_period = "5m"
reboot_cooldown = "30m"
tick = "500ms"
.EE

.TP
.B boot_grace_period
Suppresses reboot actions for a period after Watchguard starts.

.TP
.B reboot_cooldown
Suppresses repeated reboot actions after a reboot attempt.

.TP
.B tick
Main daemon loop sleep interval.

.SH COMMAND CONFIGURATION
Example:

.EX
[commands]
reboot = ["/usr/bin/systemctl", "reboot", "--force", "--force"]
restart_ssh = ["/usr/bin/systemctl", "restart", "sshd.service"]
.EE

On Ubuntu, the SSH service is usually
.B ssh.service
rather than
.BR sshd.service .

.SH OOM PLUGIN
The OOM plugin follows kernel logs through:

.EX
journalctl -kf -n0
.EE

Example:

.EX
[oom]
enabled = false

patterns = [
  "out of memory: kill process",
  "invoked oom-killer",
  "oom-killer",
  "memory cgroup out of memory"
]
.EE

Enable:

.EX
sudo watchguard enable oom
sudo systemctl restart watchguard.service
.EE

.SH SSH PLUGIN
Example:

.EX
[ssh]
enabled = false

service_check_enabled = true
service = "sshd.service"
service_check_interval = "2s"
service_fail_limit = 3
service_failure_action = "restart"

target_check_enabled = true
ssh_check_interval = "5s"
ssh_timeout = "1500ms"
ssh_fail_limit = 3
require_all = false

targets = [
  "127.0.0.1:22"
]

ssh_failure_action = "restart"
.EE

Enable:

.EX
sudo watchguard enable ssh
sudo systemctl restart watchguard.service
.EE

If
.B watchguard test --all
reports a
.B GetUnit
error, the configured SSH service name probably does not exist. Check:

.EX
systemctl status sshd.service
systemctl status ssh.service
systemctl list-unit-files | grep -E '^ssh|^sshd'
.EE

.SH NETWORK PLUGIN
Example:

.EX
[network]
enabled = false

check_interval = "5s"
timeout = "1500ms"
fail_limit = 6
require_all = false

targets = [
  "1.1.1.1:443",
  "8.8.8.8:443"
]

failure_action = "none"
.EE

Enable:

.EX
sudo watchguard enable network
sudo systemctl restart watchguard.service
.EE

Only set
.B failure_action = "reboot"
after validating that the targets are reliable for the host.

.SH DNS PLUGIN
Example:

.EX
[dns]
enabled = false

check_interval = "30s"
fail_limit = 6

server = "1.1.1.1:53"
name = "example.com"

failure_action = "none"
.EE

Enable:

.EX
sudo watchguard enable dns
sudo systemctl restart watchguard.service
.EE

.SH LOGS
Follow logs:

.EX
watchguard logs
.EE

Show current boot logs without following:

.EX
watchguard logs --boot --no-follow
.EE

Show recent logs:

.EX
watchguard logs --since "1 hour ago"
.EE

Equivalent journalctl command:

.EX
journalctl -u watchguard.service -f
.EE

.SH EXAMPLES
Run diagnostics:

.EX
watchguard doctor
.EE

Test enabled plugins:

.EX
watchguard test
.EE

Test all configured plugins:

.EX
watchguard test --all
.EE

Enable SSH monitoring:

.EX
sudo watchguard enable ssh
sudo systemctl restart watchguard.service
.EE

Enable OOM monitoring:

.EX
sudo watchguard enable oom
sudo systemctl restart watchguard.service
.EE

Show version:

.EX
watchguard version
.EE

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/watchguard
Watchguard binary.

.TP
.I /etc/watchguard/config.toml
Default configuration file.

.TP
.I /usr/lib/systemd/system/watchguard.service
Packaged systemd unit file.

.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/watchguard.service
Common path for manual systemd unit installation.

.TP
.I /usr/share/man/man8/watchguard.8
Manual page.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Command completed successfully.

.TP
.B non-zero
A command failed, a probe failed, or the configuration was invalid.

.SH TROUBLESHOOTING
.TP
.B watchguard test --all fails disabled checks
This is expected. The
.B --all
flag tests configured plugins even when disabled. Use
.B watchguard test
to test only enabled plugins.

.TP
.B SSH service GetUnit error
The configured systemd unit does not exist. Check whether the host uses
.B sshd.service
or
.BR ssh.service .

.TP
.B SSH target probe failed
Check whether port 22 is listening:

.EX
ss -tlnp | grep ':22'
.EE

